<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1322,284,350]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis box="[312,414,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Srinivasa" authorityYear="2006" box="[431,671,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Canopyana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vateriae">
<emphasis box="[431,671,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Canopyana vateriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1918" box="[1002,1103,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Carvaka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1103,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Carvaka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be differentiated by the claval venation and very distinctive male genitalia.
</paragraph>
